ANTHRAX - BENIN (02): (ATACORA) HUMAN, BOVINE, OIE
*******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 10 Apr 2013
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2013; 26(15) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=13250


Anthrax, Benin
--------------
Information received on (and dated) 10 Apr 2013 from Dr Richard Hounga Lokossou, [Director of Livestock, Ministry of Agriculture, Livestock and Fisheries], Cotonou, Benin

Summary
Report type: follow-up report No. 1
Date of start of the event: 20 Mar 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 20 Mar 2013
Report date: 10 Apr 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 10 Apr 2013
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: June 2012
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country
Related reports:
Immediate notification (22 Mar 2013)
Follow-up report no. 1 (10 Apr 2013)

New outbreaks (1):
Outbreak 1: Koudogou, Natta, Boukoumbe, Boukoumbe [Atacora]
Date of start of the outbreak: 9 Apr 2013
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 4 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: herd including a bull, a cow, a heifer and a calf

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 4 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 25 percent / 25 percent / 100 percent / 25 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive; animals in an area of anthrax-infected fields
Epidemiological comments: there was a human case in the previous outbreak, in Tabota, who has been treated and has recovered.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [available at the source URL above. The outbreak is close to the border with Togo. - Mod.MHJ]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The is the 1st report of a prior human case, fortunately recovering. The area vaccination programme is clearly progressing at its own pace.

For maps of Benin, see http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/africa/benin_admin_2007.jpg and http://healthmap.org/r/22M3.
For Togo, see http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/africa/togo_pol_2007.jpg.
For Boukoumbe, see http://www.fallingrain.com/world/BN/08/Boukoumbe.html.
It is a stone's throw from the Togo border. - Mod.MHJ]
